            "ignore": false,
            "order": 9,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "The ability of ICAE demonstrates great promise to handle long contexts, as it can save a significant amount of GPU memory when addressing long contexts without touching the existing LLM. As illustrated in Figure 6(Right), 2048-length memory slots can perform on par with 4096-token contexts. This means that conditioning on 2048 memory slots instead of the original 4096 context tokens can save about 20GB of GPU memory<sup>5</sup> with minimal quality degradation.",
            "line_with_spans": [
