            "ignore": false,
            "order": 11,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "Prompt compression and context distillation (Askell et al., 2021; Snell et al., 2022) are closely related areas to this work: Wingate et al. (2022) proposed a method to learn compact soft prompts to simulate the original natural language prompt by optimizing the KL divergence. However, this approach has a very high computational cost, as it requires performing back-propagation for each new incoming prompt to learn and obtain the compressed prompt, which severely limits its application. Qin  $\\&$ Van Durme (2023) propose Neural Agglomerative Embeddings named NUGGET, which encodes language into a compact representation for an encoder-decoder model.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
